[{"id":"VR834507","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two charged particles in the first quadrant an x y plane. The values 0, d, and 2 d are indicated on the x axis and the values 0 and d are indicated on the y axis. The first particle is located at 2 d along the x axis, and has a charge of negative 4 Q. The second particle is located at d along the y axis, and  has a charge of positive Q.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834507.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two charged particles are fixed in place in an <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x y\"><math alttext=\"x y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></math></span></span>-coordinate system, as shown in the figure. One particle has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> and is located at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the point with coordinates 0 comma d\"><math alttext=\"the point with coordinates 0 comma d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mn>0</mn></mpadded><mo>,</mo><mpadded><mi>d</mi></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>, and the other particle has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 4 Q\"><math alttext=\"negative 4 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> and is located at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the point with coordinates 2 d comma 0\"><math alttext=\"the point with coordinates 2 d comma 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mpadded><mo>,</mo><mpadded><mn>0</mn></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span>. What is the electric potential at the origin due to the two particles?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR834507_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the negative fraction k Q over d\"><math alttext=\"the negative fraction k Q over d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mpadded><mrow><mo>−</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></mrow></mpadded></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the negative fraction with numerator 4, and denominator the square root of 5, end fraction, times the fraction k Q over d\"><math alttext=\"the negative fraction with numerator 4, and denominator the square root of 5, end fraction, times the fraction k Q over d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mpadded><mrow><mo>−</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></mrow></mpadded></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the positive square root of 5, end root, times the fraction k Q over d\"><math alttext=\"the positive square root of 5, end root, times the fraction k Q over d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></mpadded></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 3 times the fraction k Q over d\"><math alttext=\"positive 3 times the fraction k Q over d\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></mpadded></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]